It is out of the question for Taiwan to seek independence;
instead, the time for Chinese union will come when both sides of the
Taiwan Strait become democratic and enjoy freedoms, Su said.

The report also pointed out the four principles that Taiwan will
uphold while conducting negotiations with the mainland over the
opening of direct transportation links. The four principles are: no
concessions on sovereignty; no depletion of public authority;
securing of the overall national interest and the people's welfare;
and government-directed negotiations only.

